<h4>Hair Transplant – What is it?</h4>
<p>Hair transplantation is a walk in-walk out surgical technique that involves moving individual hair follicles from one part of the body (the donor site) to bald or balding parts (the recipient site). It is primarily used to treat male pattern baldness.</p>

<p>The procedure only deals with the surface layers of the skin: the epidermis and dermis. The first two layers of the skin contain the hair follicles (roots). The removal and transplanting of hair is a straightforward minor surgical procedure carried out under local anesthesia. It only takes a few hours but the complex part of hair transplantation is the artistry required by the hair transplant surgeon who determines the shape of the hairline and the overall hair direction.</p>

<hr />
<h4>Hair Transplant – Our Solutions</h4>
<p><strong>Single follicular unit (FUHT Method)- </strong>This procedure is the most effective & cosmetically acceptable method. We take a strip of hairs from the patient's back area of the scalp. After the removal of that strip from the scalp, single follicular units are dissected & under local anesthesia these hairs are implanted in the recipient . A scar is left behind in the form of a fine thin line at the graft site, which is hardly visible. The implanted hairs fall within 3 months but then start growing, full regrowth takes around 8-10 months. These hairs are permanent & grow forever. Natural looking hairline can be achieved by this method. This procedure is best for average to extreme balding cases since it allows several grafts to be transplanted in a single session</p>


<p><strong>Follicular Unit Extraction (FUE)/Stitch less surgery- </strong>In FUE, instead of a strip, single units are extracted either from the scalp or beard or other body parts with very fine micro punches. Suturing is not required in this case..The punches are so fine that the healing is very fast & without any scarring. </p>
